Spatial cell clustering of Vizgen data by MEcell

Qi Liu

19 June, 2025

  • Load the library and the seurat object
  • Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering
  • Cell types of interest: hippocampus, VSMC, and microglia

Load the library and the seurat object

library(MEcell)
library(ggplot2)

# The data have already been SCT-normalized and RunPCA using Seurat
#The Seurat object contains raw counts,SCT-normalized data, and PCA embeddings

#To avoid timeout error, we increase the timeout limit
options(timeout = 300) 
obj<-readRDS(url("https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/b1dtjqpev6436fqui858h/vizgen_brain.rds?rlkey=kvwhjg9bi5ockiktf26a28bti&dl=1"))

Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering

# build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell)
obj<-MEcell(obj)

#clustering on the MEcell SNN graph
obj<-FindClusters(obj,graph.name = "MEcell",verbose = F)

#visualizing cell clustering 
ImageDimPlot(obj,group.by="MEcell_res.0.8")+ ggtitle("MEcell clustering")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

Cell types of interest: hippocampus, VSMC, and microglia

#Hippocampus 
ImageDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(23,25,26)])+ ggtitle("Hippocampus")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

#VSMC and microglia
ImageDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(24,27)])+ ggtitle("VSMC and microglia")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

#VSMC and microglia marker genes from single-cell RNAseq 
DotPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(24,27)],features=c("C1qb","C1qa","Selplg","Cx3cr1","P2ry12","Lmod1","Gpr20","Pln","Myh11"))
